records.addlTxt:
Defendant Anthony G Knutowski in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   Debra Lynn Blasius appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed by operation of law.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed  Sentence of 

6 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 113 days)
- 3 Years of Initial Confinement
- 3 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- Be involved in a 12 step program and least 2 times a week within 30 days of release an within 60 days obtain a mentor/sponsor;
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.

FINE:  $2277.00 
DNA Surcharge: $250.00
DNA Sample ordered.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 to be paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to  Oconomowoc Police Department.
(To be paid as a condition of extended supervision at the rate of $ 100.00  per month commencing the 6th month of extended supervision)
DL REVOCATION:   36 months.

IGNITITION INTERLOCK:  36 months.

Defendant to attend the Victim Impact Panel on: Within 90 days of release onto extended supervision

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
